==English==
===Noun===
#Lower section of a road or geological feature.
#:There is a dip in the road ahead.
#Tank or trough where cattle or sheep are immersed in chemicals to kill parasites.
#'''Dip Stick''' Removable rod used to check level of fluid in a container. (Typically oil in an engine).

===Verb===
#Lower into a liquid.
#:''Dip your biscuit into your tea''.
#Lower a light's beam.
#:Dip your lights as you meet an oncoming car.
#Treat cattle or sheep by immersion in chemical solution.
#:The farmer is going to dip the cattle today.
#To use a Dip stick to check oil level in an engine.